e`, `--continue`, `--share` |\\n    16→| Config directory | PASS | `~/.copilot/` (user-level), `.github/hooks/` (repo-level) |\\n    17→| Documentation | PASS | docs.github.com/en/copilot/reference/hooks-configuration |\\n    18→\\n    19→## Binary\\n    20→\\n    21→- Name: `copilot`\\n    22→- Version: `0.0.420` (GA as of 2026-02-25)\\n    23→- Install: `brew install copilot-cli` or `npm install -g @github/copilot`\\n    24→\\n    25→## Hook Mechanism\\n    26→\\n    27→- Config file: `.github/hooks/*.json` (all JSON files in directory are auto-discovered)\\n    28→- Our file: `.github/hooks/entire.json` (dedicated file, avoids conflicts)\\n    29→- Config format: JSON\\n    30→- Hook registration: Array of hook entries per event name, each with `type: \\\"command\\\"` and `bash` field\\n    31→\\n    32→### Hook Config Format\\n    33→\\n    34→```json\\n    35→{\\n    36→  \\\"version\\\": 1,\\n    37→  \\\"hooks\\\": {\\n    38→    \\\"hookName\\\": [\\n    39→      {\\n    40→        \\\"type\\\": \\\"command\\\",\\n    41→        \\\"bash\\\": \\\"entire hooks copilot-cli hook-name\\\"\\n    42→      }\\n    43→    ]\\n    44→  }\\n    45→}\\n    46→```\\n    47→\\n    48→Note: Uses `bash` key (not `command` like Claude Code/Gemini). Also supports `powershell` for Windows. Each entry can have optional `cwd`, `timeoutSec` (default 30), `env`, and `comment` fields.\\n    49→\\n    50→### Hook Names and Event Mapping\\n    51→\\n    52→| Native Hook Name | When It Fires | Stdin Payload Fields | Entire EventType |\\n    53→|-----------------|---------------|---------------------|-----------------|\\n    54→| `userPromptSubmitted` | User submits a prompt | `timestamp`, `cwd`, `sessionId`, `prompt` | `TurnStart` |\\n    55→| `sessionStart` | Agent session begins/resumes | `timestamp`, `cwd`, `sessionId`, `source`, `initialPrompt` | `SessionStart` |\\n    56→| `agentStop` | Agent finishes a turn | `timestamp`, `cwd`, `sessionId`, `transcriptPath`, `stopReason` | `TurnEnd` |\\n    57→| `sessionEnd` | Session completed/terminated | `timestamp`, `cwd`, `sessionId`, `reason` | `SessionEnd` |\\n    58→| `subagentStop` | Subagent finishes | `timestamp`, `cwd`, `sessionId`, *(TBD — needs capture)* | `SubagentEnd` |\\n    59→| `preToolUse` | Before tool execution | *(TBD — needs capture)* | *(pass-through)* |\\n    60→| `postToolUse` | After tool execution | *(TBD — needs capture)* | *(pass-through)* |\\n    61→| `errorOccurred` | Error during execution | *(TBD — needs capture)* | *(pass-through)* |\\n    62→\\n    63→**Event ordering quirk:** `userPromptSubmitted` fires BEFORE `sessionStart` on the first prompt. This matches Claude Code's behavior and the framework's session phase state machine handles it correctly (TurnStart can arrive before SessionStart).\\n    64→\\n    65→**Valid Entire EventTypes:** `SessionStart`, `TurnStart`, `TurnEnd`, `Compaction`, `SessionEnd`, `SubagentStart`, `SubagentEnd`\\n    66→\\n    67→### Hook Input Payloads (Captured)\\n    68→\\n    69→**userPromptSubmitted:**\\n    70→```json\\n    71→{\\\"timestamp\\\":1771480081360,\\\"cwd\\\":\\\"/path/to/repo\\\",\\\"sessionId\\\":\\\"b0ff98c0-8e01-4b73-bf92-9649b139931b\\\",\\\"prompt\\\":\\\"hi\\\"}\\n    72→```\\n    73→\\n    74→**sessionStart:**\\n    75→```json\\n    76→{\\\"timestamp\\\":1771480081383,\\\"cwd\\\":\\\"/path/to/repo\\\",\\\"sessionId\\\":\\\"b0ff98c0-8e01-4b73-bf92-9649b139931b\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"new\\\",\\\"initialPrompt\\\":\\\"hi\\\"}\\n    77→```\\n    78→\\n    79→**agentStop:**\\n    80→```json\\n    81→{\\\"timestamp\\\":1771480085412,\\\"cwd\\\":\\\"/path/to/repo\\\",\\\"sessionId\\\":\\\"b0ff98c0-8e01-4b73-bf92-9649b139931b\\\",\\\"transcriptPath\\\":\\\"/home/user/.copilot/session-state/b0ff98c0-8e01-4b73-bf92-9649b139931b/events.jsonl\\\",\\\"stopReason\\\":\\\"end_turn\\\"}\\n    82→```\\n    83→\\n    84→**sessionEnd:**\\n    85→```json\\n    86→{\\\"timestamp\\\":1771480085425,\\\"cwd\\\":\\\"/path/to/repo\\\",\\\"sessionId\\\":\\\"b0ff98c0-8e01-4b73-bf92-9649b139931b\\\",\\\"reason\\\":\\\"complete\\\"}\\n    87→```\\n    88→\\n    89→## Transcript\\n    90→\\n    91→- Location: `~/.copilot/session-state/<sessionId>/events.jsonl`\\n    92→- Format: JSONL (one JSON object per line)\\n    93→- Session ID extraction: `sessionId` field in hook payloads (UUID format)\\n    94→- Session ID format: UUID (`b0ff98c0-8e01-4b73-bf92-9649b139931b`)\\n    95→\\n    96→### Transcript Entry Schema\\n    97→\\n    98→Each line has: `type`, `data`, `id` (UUID), `timestamp` (ISO 8601), `parentId`\\n    99→\\n   100→**Event types observed:**\\n   101→- `session.start` — Session metadata (sessionId, version, producer, copilotVersion, context)\\n   102→- `user.message` — User messages (`content`, `transformedContent`, `attachments`, `interactionId`)\\n   103→- `assistant.turn_start` — Start of assistant turn (`turnId`, `interactionId`)\\n   104→- `assistant.message` — Assistant response (`content`, `toolRequests[]`, `reasoningText`)\\n   105→- `tool.execution_complete` — Tool result (`toolCallId`, `toolTelemetry.properties.filePaths` (JSON-encoded string array), `linesAdded`, `linesRemoved`)\\n   106→- `assistant.turn_end` — End of assistant turn (`turnId`)\\n   107→\\n   108→**Example entries:**\\n   109→```jsonl\\n   110→{\\\"type\\\":\\\"session.start\\\",\\\"data\\\":{\\\"sessionId\\\":\\\"4de47255-...\\\",\\\"version\\\":1,\\\"producer\\\":\\\"copilot-agent\\\",\\\"copilotVersion\\\":\\\"0.0.420\\\",\\\"startTime\\\":\\\"2026-03-02T01:11:45.379Z\\\",\\\"context\\\":{\\\"cwd\\\":\\\"/path\\\",\\\"gitRoot\\\":\\\"/path\\\",\\\"branch\\\":\\\"main\\\",\\\"repository\\\":\\\"org/repo\\\"}},\\\"id\\\":\\\"c1c1...\\\",\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"2026-03-02T01:11:45.421Z\\\",\\\"parentId\\\":null}\\n   111→{\\\"type\\\":\\\"user.message\\\",\\\"data\\\":{\\\"content\\\":\\\"exit\\\",\\\"transformedContent\\\":\\\"...\\\",\\\"attachments\\\":[],\\\"interactionId\\\":\\\"6cd0...\\\"},\\\"id\\\":\\\"20fa...\\\",\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"...\\\",\\\"parentId\\\":\\\"00ac...\\\"}\\n   112→{\\\"type\\\":\\\"assistant.turn_start\\\",\\\"data\\\":{\\\"turnId\\\":\\\"0\\\",\\\"interactionId\\\":\\\"6cd0...\\\"},\\\"id\\\":\\\"3b61...\\\",\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"...\\\",\\\"parentId\\\":\\\"20fa...\\\"}\\n   113→{\\\"type\\\":\\\"assistant.message\\\",\\\"data\\\":{\\\"messageId\\\":\\\"a078...\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"To exit...\\\",\\\"toolRequests\\\":[],\\\"interactionId\\\":\\\"6cd0...\\\",\\\"reasoningText\\\":\\\"...\\\"},\\\"id\\\":\\\"c892...\\\",\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"...\\\",\\\"parentId\\\":\\\"aaeb...\\\"}\\n   114→{\\\"type\\\":\\\"assistant.turn_end\\\",\\\"data\\\":{\\\"turnId\\\":\\\"0\\\"},\\\"id\\\":\\\"0ae4...\\\",\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"...\\\",\\\"parentId\\\":\\\"4989...\\\"}\\n   115→```\\n   116→\\n   117→### Tool Usage in Transcripts\\n   118→\\n   119→The `assistant.message` entries have a `toolRequests` array with tool call IDs. After each tool executes, a `tool.execution_complete` event is emitted with `toolTelemetry.properties.filePaths`, where `filePaths` is a string containing a JSON array of file paths modified by that tool call. The `TranscriptAnalyzer` implementation parses this `filePaths` property to extract modified files for checkpoint metadata.\\n   120→\\n   121→**Note:** Token usage is NOT available in the Copilot CLI JSONL format. The transcript events do not include input/output token counts or cost information, so `TokenCalculator` is not implemented.\\n   122→\\n   123→### Transcript Position\\n   124→\\n   125→Position = line count (JSONL format). Use `agent.ChunkJSONL()` / `agent.ReassembleJSONL()` for chunking.\\n   126→\\n   127→### TranscriptAnalyzer\\n   128→\\n   129→The `TranscriptAnalyzer` interface is implemented for Copilot CLI, providing:\\n   130→- `GetTranscriptPosition` — counts JSONL lines (lightweight, no JSON parsing)\\n   131→- `ExtractModifiedFilesFromOffset` — collects `filePaths` from `tool.execution_complete` events after a given line offset\\n   132→- `ExtractPrompts` — collects `content` from `user.message` events\\n   133→- `ExtractSummary` — returns the `content` of the last `assistant.message` event\\n   134→\\n   135→## Session State Directory\\n   136→\\n   137→```\\n   138→~/.copilot/session-state/<sessionId>/\\n   139→├── events.jsonl          # Transcript (JSONL)\\n   140→├── workspace.yaml        # Workspace metadata (cwd, git info, summary)\\n   141→├── checkpoints/          # Agent's own checkpoints\\n   142→├── files/                # File snapshots\\n   143→├── research/             # Research data\\n   144→└── rewind-snapshots/     # Agent's rewind snapshots\\n   145→```\\n   146→\\n   147→## Config Preservation\\n   148→\\n   149→- Hook config is in `.github/hooks/*.json` — each file is auto-discovered\\n   150→- We create a **dedicated** `.github/hooks/entire.json` file, leaving other hook files untouched\\n   151→- No need for read-modify-write of existing files\\n   152→- If `entire.json` already exists, read-modify-write to preserve any user additions\\n   153→\\n   154→## CLI Flags\\n   155→\\n   156→- Non-interactive prompt: `copilot -p \\\"prompt\\\" --allow-all-tools`\\n   157→- Interactive with initial prompt: `copilot -i \\\"prompt\\\"`\\n   158→- Interactive mode: `copilot`\\n   159→- Resume most recent: `copilot --continue`\\n   160→- Resume specific: `copilot --resume <sessionId>`\\n   161→- Autopilot (no confirmations): `copilot --autopilot`\\n   162→- Config directory: `--config-dir <dir>` (default: `~/.copilot`)\\n   163→- Relevant env vars: `COPILOT_ALLOW_ALL` (equivalent to `--allow-all-tools`)\\n   164→\\n   165→## Presence Detection\\n   166→\\n   167→- No repo-level `.copilot/` directory (unlike other agents)\\n   168→- `DetectPresence` delegates to `AreHooksInstalled`, which reads `.github/hooks/entire.json` and checks if any hook entry has an Entire command prefix (`entire ` or `go run ${COPILOT_PROJECT_DIR}/cmd/entire/main.go `)\\n   169→- Simply having a `.github/hooks/` directory is NOT sufficient -- the directory must contain `entire.json` with Entire hook entries\\n   170→- Alternative: check for `copilot` binary in PATH\\n   171→\\n   172→## Protected Directories\\n   173→\\n   174→- `.github` — contains hook configs (committed to repo, unlikely to be affected by rewind)\\n   175→- No agent-specific repo directory to protect\\n   176→\\n   177→## Subagent Lifecycle\\n   178→\\n   179→Copilot CLI has **one-sided** subagent hooks: `subagentStop` fires but `subagentStart` does NOT\\n   180→(tested by registering the hook — Copilot CLI ignores it). The transcript does contain\\n   181→`subagent.started` / `subagent.completed` events with `toolCallId`, but these are not\\n   182→surfaced as hooks.\\n   183→\\n   184→The `preToolUse` / `postToolUse` hooks fire with `toolName: \\\"task\\\"` for subagent lifecycle,\\n   185→which could be used as an alternative mechanism for `SubagentStart`/`SubagentEnd` in the future.\\n   186→\\n   187→Because there is no `SubagentStart` hook, the framework cannot capture pre-task state (untracked\\n   188→files snapshot). The `handleLifecycleSubagentEnd` dispatcher falls back to the session's\\n   189→pre-prompt state to avoid spurious task checkpoints from pre-existing untracked files\\n   190→(e.g., `.github/hooks/entire.json`).\\n   191→\\n   192→## Gaps & Limitations\\n   193→\\n   194→- No `Compaction` event — Copilot CLI doesn't appear to have a context compaction hook\\n   195→- No `SubagentStart` hook — only `subagentStop` fires; framework falls back to pre-prompt state\\n   196→- `subagentStop` payload fields beyond `timestamp`/`cwd`/`sessionId` not yet fully captured\\n   197→- `preToolUse` / `postToolUse` payloads not yet leveraged (could provide SubagentStart equivalent)\\n   198→- Tool request schema in transcripts needs verification with a real tool-using session\\n   199→- `transcriptPath` only available in `agentStop` hook — `userPromptSubmitted` and 